A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a mailbox transformed into a sleek timeline, with colorful envelopes floating out and arranging themselves into neat horizontal date-grouped rows against a warm cream background. The envelopes cast soft shadows and appear to be sorting themselves automatically, some still mid-flight while others have settled into their organized positions. The scene has a retro advertising aesthetic with muted oranges, teals, and browns, grainy texture, and slightly faded edges reminiscent of mid-century modern design posters. A subtle geometric grid pattern underlies the composition, suggesting structure and organization emerging from chaos.
